I"¼<p>Memoirs theme has Prism highlighter integrated. I will show you in this post a few examples of how it looks if you are a developer planning to add pieces of code on your website.</p>

<h4 id="html">HTML</h4>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;li class="ml-1 mr-1"&gt;
    &lt;a target="_blank" href="#"&gt;
    &lt;i class="fab fa-twitter"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
</code></pre>

<h4 id="css">CSS</h4>

<pre><code class="language-css">.highlight .c {
    color: #999988;
    font-style: italic; 
}
.highlight .err {
    color: #a61717;
    background-color: #e3d2d2; 
}
</code></pre>

<h4 id="js">JS</h4>

<pre><code class="language-js">// alertbar later
$(document).scroll(function () {
    var y = $(this).scrollTop();
    if (y &gt; 280) {
        $('.alertbar').fadeIn();
    } else {
        $('.alertbar').fadeOut();
    }
});
</code></pre>

<h4 id="python">Python</h4>

<pre><code class="language-python">print("Hello World")
</code></pre>

<h4 id="ruby">Ruby</h4>

<pre><code class="language-ruby">require 'redcarpet'
markdown = Redcarpet.new("Hello World!")
puts markdown.to_html
</code></pre>

<h4 id="c">C</h4>

<pre><code class="language-c">printf("Hello World");
